You could call mine a salaryman's take on Gary Danko since I ate there under circumstances different than most reviewers. It's around the corner from a place where I stay several times a year for work, and tonight I decided to give it a try. It was easy enough to get a single place at the bar early on a Monday evening when several seats were open. I savored my meal, read a recent New Yorker magazine, and was in and out in about an hour. I had no problem deciding what to order after reading the reviews: the seafood risotto, branzino and stuffed quail. The branzino was dry and disappointing but the risotto and quail were delicious yet had a certain paint-by-the-numbers quality by which I mean they featured rich, complex ingredients executed in a formulaic way. That's as compared to highlighting a single ingredient, or making adjustments based on what proteins and vegetables were particular inspiring when they arrived at the kitchen today. By comparison, the best parts of the meal were the unadvertised bits at the beginning and the end. The amuse bouche was a fabulous gazpacho with abundant sherry vinegar and a frisson of toasted basil chiffonade. Along with the check they brought out a varied selection of petits fours, all delicious, which are doubtless meant to be shared by a table but were happily consumed by yours truly. (No reason to order a separate dessert when this bounty is right in front of you.) By the way, the little treat of a mini-cake to take away seems to have been discontinued. I had a Dewar's on the rocks with a twist beforehand which was not particularly generous and featured an enormous ice cube that made it hard to get at the Scotch. The list of wines by the glass was surprisingly meager and quite costly compared to food prices so I ordered a Lagunitas IPA which served me well. This is still an excellent meal and a good value for the setting at $81 for my three courses and I'll likely be back. But transcendent, it was not.

First time at Gary Danko last night for my mom's 70th birthday and it did not disappoint at all. Pricey is an underestimate so be prepared drop some dollars for some some amazing food and impeccable service from everyone on the staff. You get to choose between a prefix 5 course, or you can pick a 3 course, 4 course, or 5 course on your own. Mix and matching appetizers, seafood, meat, and dessert. We loved the seared foie gras, seared scallops, salmon medallions, glazed oysters, pork loin, and duck breast. We all thought the only thing that disappointed surprisingly was the Lobster......really lacking any flavor and size, but we warned prior to that and did not listen. Also the complimentary bread and butter was underwhelming. They really should step up with some heartier, fresh out of the oven bread and warmer salted butter. Those are nit picks though. Overall worth every penny for the experience and thank you guys for making my Mom happy beyond words. She loved it and the extra dessert with bday candle was a beatific touch.

Flavor for all categories complimented each other. Also bonus, service was fantastic. We will definitely recommend and come back again.

This place refreshed my memory of what fine dining truly entails. #sanfrancisco #restaurantreview In LA, the hot restaurants have inventive food, cool decor and the expected high prices, but also snotty service. Gary Danko reminds me that when you're paying $100+ pp, that should come with superb customer service. The staff was all helpful, patient and attentive. Our water glasses were never empty and nor were our bread plates. Our dishes were timed perfectly. There's scented soap and lotion in the restroom. But more importantly, the food is excellent. Carefully constructed plates in which you are compelled to put together perfect mouthfuls with every ingredient. Wide selection spanning vegetarian to sea to land. Even their dessert menu is larger than your average nice restaurant's, and they have a cheese cart stacked with exotic cheeses. Romantic ambience, but not stuffy. Classic and traditional, but suitable for younger folks as well. Recommend the fois gras, the glazed oysters, the risotto with seafood, the duck breast, the soft shell crab, the coconut semi freddo... There isn't a dish we ate that we wouldn't recommend.

We celebrated our 21st anniversary here and they made it a truly special evening for us. We each ordered the three course menu and were stuffed. They brought us both a complimentary small bite to start and finished the meal with a nice assortment of cookies as well as a special desert for our anniversary. We particularly enjoyed the seafood curry, Dungeness crab salad, risotto, sea bass and scallops. The service is unmatched. Such wonderful presentation of the food and attention to detail. We found a very affordable bubbly on the menu. We talked to several of the folks around us who were all long-time regulars and it was obvious they still love this place. I highly recommend it for any special occasion.

I LOVE that Gary Danko lets you create your own tasting menu. You can choose 3, 4, or 5 courses and mix and match from any category, making the perfect meal for your tastes. All of the food is absolutely delicious, service is wonderful, the wine list is astonishing, and the cheese trolley will change your life. Absolutely a lovely dinner! GD has earned their Michelin star for sure. :) Also - their portion sizes are marvelous! You definitely won't leave hungry, and they will spoil you with sweet treats and a lovely breakfast cake to go for the next morning. One of the best meals of my life so far! (5 course dinner for two including tax, tip, and the cheapest bottle of wine on the list came to $390 for those who are wondering about cost.)

Started with foie gras which was excellent paired with rhubarb. The sweet, acidic tang of the rhubarb complimented the foie gras perfectly.

What have you done to me Gary ... I can't stop thinking about you now. Thank you for taking my taste buds on a magical ride through heaven! You're one of the best restaurants I have ever been to! My friend and I went for the 4-course meal and had the following: Appetizers - Dungeness Crab Salad (w/ Avocado, Citrus, Bulgar and Mustard-Tarragon Vinaigrette). One of the best salads I tasted hands down. Very fresh, crab was flavored perfectly, and very well-portioned. - Seared Foie Gras (w/ Caramelized Onions, and Vanilla Poached Rhubarb). Usually I'm very picky with food, I don't really like eating duck or goose liver. But my friend ordered it, and I had a bite, and oh boy, I fell in love! It literally melts in your mouth, super flavorful and delicious! You need to get this!!! Fish and Seafood - Coconut Thai Curry (w/ Shrimp, Calamari, Lobster, Scallops, Scallions and Shiitake Mushrooms). Cooked to perfection! Great balance of sweetness and spice. My personal favorite is the seared scallops in this! Tastes AMAZING with the sauce, and it will sure give your taste buds a good time. - Roast Maine Lobster (w/ Potato Purée, White Beech Mushrooms, Edamame and Tarragon). My friend ordered this and I had a few bites, and oh man, it tastes absolutely divine! I was hoping my friend would get full from the appetizer so I can have more of the lobster. Tastes amazing! Meat - Seared Filet of Beef (w/ Swiss Chard, Potatoes, Shallot Marmalade and Bordelaise Butter). My friend and I both ordered this. Cooked perfectly, well seasoned, and super flavorful and juicy on the inside. Desserts! - Crème Fraîche Cheesecake (w/ Citrus, Spiced Pecans and Blood Orange Sorbet). My favorite dessert is the cheesecake, so when I saw this on the menu, I knew I had to order it. Decision well made! Tastes sweet (but not too sweet) and tangy. Super creamy, but surprisingly light! Dip your cheesecake with the strawberry sorbet and ermahhgerrd, tastes like droplets of heaven. Oh Gary Danko, you always leave me wanting more. Thank you for an amazing experience. Until next time!

    What have you done to me Gary ... I can't stop thinking about you now. Thank you for taking my taste buds on a magical ride through heaven! You're one of the best restaurants I have ever been to!

    My friend and I went for the 4-course meal and had the following:

    Appetizers
    - Dungeness Crab Salad (w/ Avocado, Citrus, Bulgar and Mustard-Tarragon Vinaigrette). One of the best salads I tasted hands down. Very fresh, crab was flavored perfectly, and very well-portioned.
    - Seared Foie Gras (w/ Caramelized Onions, and Vanilla Poached Rhubarb). Usually I'm very picky with food, I don't really like eating duck or goose liver. But my friend ordered it, and I had a bite, and oh boy, I fell in love! It literally melts in your mouth, super flavorful and delicious! You need to get this!!!

    Fish and Seafood
    - Coconut Thai Curry (w/ Shrimp, Calamari, Lobster, Scallops, Scallions and Shiitake Mushrooms). Cooked to perfection! Great balance of sweetness and spice. My personal favorite is the seared scallops in this! Tastes AMAZING with the sauce, and it will sure give your taste buds a good time.
    - Roast Maine Lobster (w/ Potato Purée, White Beech Mushrooms, Edamame and Tarragon). My friend ordered this and I had a few bites, and oh man, it tastes absolutely divine! I was hoping my friend would get full from the appetizer so I can have more of the lobster. Tastes amazing!

    Meat
    - Seared Filet of Beef (w/ Swiss Chard, Potatoes, Shallot Marmalade and Bordelaise Butter). My friend and I both ordered this. Cooked perfectly, well seasoned, and super flavorful and juicy on the inside.

    Desserts!
    - Crème Fraîche Cheesecake (w/ Citrus, Spiced Pecans and Blood Orange Sorbet). My favorite dessert is the cheesecake, so when I saw this on the menu, I knew I had to order it. Decision well made! Tastes sweet (but not too sweet) and tangy. Super creamy, but surprisingly light! Dip your cheesecake with the strawberry sorbet and ermahhgerrd, tastes like droplets of heaven.

    Oh Gary Danko, you always leave me wanting more. Thank you for an amazing experience. Until next time!

    I came here after just going through an AWFUL breakup. My dad took me to try and cheer me up, and I had been crying all day and not even feeling like going out. I was hesitant to sit through a six course dinner.

    That being said, this place lifted my spirits in an incredible way and, will I give Gary Danko the credit for helping me get over my ex? Maybe........MAYBE. ;) This was hands down the most impeccable and wonderful dining experience I've had the pleasure of enjoying.

    Our server was quirky, personable, and so great at knowing when to come by the table and exactly how much conversation to have. What a great hire. He was smart, spot-on with his recommendations, and when I mentioned that I had a rough day, he brought me an extra chocolate dessert! I will probably never forget how all of the staff was attentive, quick to fill water, and clear away plates. The only other thing I can compare this to is a well-oiled sports team. Watching the waiters and service staff seamlessly work together is something that this establishment should be very, very proud of. I hope your staff is paid well.

    We each had 6 courses, each was more amazing than the last. I had the aspargus, the seared tuna, the pork tenderloin, the filet mignon, and like 2 desserts. I love how much freedom they give you to choose your courses. We shared a bottle of wine and had a cocktail to start, so the final bill was a little pricey, but I think it was worth it.

    I left with a little nugget in a goodie bag, and just barely two spoonfuls of leftover pork. They even bagged that up for me and encouraged me to take it home. I dream of this place. Thank you for the best meal I've had in my life!

    We were lucky and got in from the waiting list 5 hours before the reservation time which was a welcome surprise for my boyfriend's birthday! EVERY single server, bartender, & host/hostess was great, super friendly, and made us feel very welcome.

    I love the concept of the menu itself! You can choose between 3 - 5 courses. However, what makes Gary Dank different is that you can choose your courses from ANY type of meal instead of 1 appetizer, 1 entree, & 1 dessert. You can choose to have 3 appetizers, 1 entree, & 1 dessert, or 5 different entrees! Genius!

    Being my first time, I of course opted for the 5 course meal while my boyfriend got a more modest 3 course meal for his birthday.

    My meal:
    Course1: Sweet Corn Soup with Dungeness Crab, Piquillo Peppers, Biscuit and Chives
    DELICIOUS. I LOVE Corn. I LOVE Crab (and there is a generous amount of crab!!).

    Course 2: Risotto with Rock Shrimp, Dungeness Crab, Shimeji Mushrooms, Corn and Roasted Tomatoes
    Best risotto I've ever had. Hands down. Seasoned perfectly. The textures were amazing together with the vegetables and seafood.

    Course 3: Pan Seared Bass with Israeli Couscous, Zucchini, Basil, Meyer Lemon, Pinenuts and Sauce Marechal
    Bass was seared perfectly. Couscous wasn't anything special, but I was getting full so I didn't eat too much of it anyways.

    Course 4: Roasted Pork Tenderloin with Pork Belly, Carrot-Ginger Puree, Fava Beans, Peas, Piquillo Peppers and Pickled Ramps
    Pork was delicious, Pork Belly tasted like a thick fat slice of heavenly bacon!!

    I was super full by this time, but still had stomache for my 5th course:

    Trio of Caramel Brulee: Peach, Vanilla, & Bourbon. YUM!

    Will definiltey be coming back more often!
